remarks:
Aeschines speculates that Demosthenes will tell the jurors that there have been four periods in which he has intervened in politics: 
1. the time of the war with Philip over Amphipolis, which he defines as ending with the peace and alliance proposed by Philocrates, with Demosthenes' support; 
2. the time when the Athenians kept the peace, which ended when the same rhetor - Demosthenes - put an end to the peace and proposed war; 
3. during the war; 
4. the present day. 
For other references to the Peace of Philocrates see also oath id 2517.

