remarks:
Aeschines recounts the benefits this peace allegedly brought to Athens: 
1. 7000 talents of silver were deposited on the Acropolis; 
2. they acquired tribute of 1200 talents per annum; 
3. they acquired more than three hundred ships; 
4. they were holding the Chersonese, Naxos and more than two thirds of Euboea; 
5. they sent out other colonies. 
Aeschines has largely lifted these statements from Andocides, On the Peace with Sparta 8-9 (oath id 2388). For other references to the Peace of Nicias and its impact see also oath id 1681.

