remarks:
Andocides states that the Athenians received the following benefits from the Peace of Nicias: 
1. 7000 talents of silver were deposited on the Acropolis; 
2. they acquired more than three hundred ships; 
3. they were receiving an annual tribute of more than 1200 talents; 
4. they were holding the Chersonese, Naxos and more than two thirds of Euboea; 
5. they held other colonies. 
These statements seem to reflect the situation in 431 better than that of 421 (and even so the figure of 1200 talents must include other sources of revenue besides the tribute); see Edwards ad loc. Andocides observes that despite these alleged benefits the Athenians were persuaded by the Argives to again go to war against the Spartans. 
For other references to the Peace of Nicias and its impact see also oath id 1681.

