remarks:
Andocides states that ten men were sent to Sparta to negotiate this peace treaty. 
He states that the Athenians gained the following benefits from the peace: 
1. the democracy was raised high; 
2. they deposited one thousand talents in the Acropolis to be kept as a special reserve; 
3. they built one hundred triremes, also as a reserve; 
4. they built shipsheds; 
5. they established a force of 1200 horsemen; 
6. they built the southern (usually called the middle) Long Wall. 
Some of these things were actually done before the Thirty Years' Peace (4) or after it had broken down (2, 3), 
For other references to the Thirty Years' Peace see oath id 1524.

