remarks:
Aeschines refers to this peace, saying that the Athenians sent Andocides and other ambassadors to Sparta to conduct the negotiations. He says that the Athenians kept the peace, but in reality the peace lasted for only fifteen years. 
Aeschines argues that the peace brought prosperity to the Athenians and that during the peace: 
1. they deposited one hundred talent in the Acropolis; 
2. they built one hundred triremes to keep in reserve; 
3. they built shipsheds; 
4. they established a force of 1200 horsemen. 
5. no man undertook to overthrow the democracy. 
Aeschines has largely lifted these statements from Andocides, On the Peace with Sparta 6-7 (oath id 2384). For other references to the Thirty Years' Peace see oath id 1524.

