remarks:
Aeschines gives his interpretation of the events at the time of the conclusion of the peace: 
1. Demosthenes convinces the Athenians to include an alliance in the peace agreement; 
2. Philocrates proposes the motion after Demosthenes persuades the demos by dragging Antipater into the assembly; 
3. Demosthenes and Philocrates then betray Cersobleptes by proposing that those in the synod should give their oaths to the ambassadors from Philip, because Cersobleptes had no representative in the synod. 
For other references to the Peace of Philocrates see also oath id 2517.

